A total of 566 HIV-positive individuals were followed for 2140.08 person-years, giving a TB incidence density rate of 6.82/100 person-years (146, 25.8%). The highest incidence was observed within the first year of follow-up. Independent determinants were large family size (adjusted HR (AHR) 1.783, 95% CI 1.113–2.855), lower baseline CD4 (AHR 2.568, 95% CI 1.602–4.116), and baseline body mass index <18.5 kg/m2 (AHR 1.907, 95% CI 1.530–2.690). Being enrolled in antiretroviral treatment (AHR 0.066, 95% CI 0.045–0.98) and taking isoniazid prophylaxis treatment (AHR 0.202, 95% CI 0.108–0.380) had a protective effect.
