keywords = "Pneumococcal infections, Pneumococcal vaccines, Pediatric immunization, Immunization programs, Population health",
abstract = "Objectives
This study was performed to evaluate the vaccine effectiveness (VE) of protein conjugated pneumococcal vaccines (PCV) in children with regard to all-cause pneumonia (ACP), pneumococcal pneumonia (PP), invasive pneumococcal disease (IPD), and acute otitis media (AOM), in a country where the unvaccinated group is very small.
