A total of 487 TB HCWs were recruited at the 31 TB-designated hospitals; 33.9% of them tested positive for LTBI. At the institutional level, a low TB epidemic level, regular infection control training for HCWs, and regular maintenance of ultraviolet disinfection equipment were found to be significantly associated with a lower LTBI rate among HCWs. At the individual level, alcohol use, a greater number of years working on TB, and a longer weekly duration of contact with TB patients were identified as associated factors for LTBI among HCWs.
